[{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/911749131","html_url":"https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6643#issuecomment-911749131","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6643","id":911749131,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAFH-b842WDAL","user":{"login":"obigu","id":1794492,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTQ0OTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1794492?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu","html_url":"https://github.com/obigu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-09-02T14:30:07Z","updated_at":"2021-09-02T14:30:07Z","body":"Yeah, current implementation is wrong, `getNativeOrientation()` docs states it returns that concept of \"natural\" device orientation (not the actual orientation) which is a thing on Android because the rotation provided by the API is device dependant and relative to that natural orientation, but not on iOS. \r\n\r\nOn iOS `getRotation()` already returns the real orientation being `0` when it's portrait so I think `getNativeOrientation()` should just return `Orientation.Portrait` and that way apps can use the same logic on both platforms.\r\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/911749131/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"obigu","id":1794492,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTQ0OTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1794492?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu","html_url":"https://github.com/obigu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/911806546","html_url":"https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6643#issuecomment-911806546","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6643","id":911806546,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAFH-b842WRBS","user":{"login":"muratmat","id":507813,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUwNzgxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/507813?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat","html_url":"https://github.com/muratmat","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-09-02T15:26:02Z","updated_at":"2021-09-02T15:26:02Z","body":"On iOS `getNativeOrientation` returns Portrait if the current rotation (i.e. the value returned by `getRotation`) is 90 or 270, else it returns Landscape. So, imagine to handle device rotation within the resize method: how can I handle the event correctly if:\r\n\r\n- I can get the current rotation using `getRotation()`\r\n- But I cannot know the native device orientation\r\n\r\nFor example, lets say `getRotation` has returned 90. How can I know if the device is a native portrait device being rotated by 90 degrees or if the device is a portrait device being rotated by 90 degrees? In the general case the behavior that the application must have can be different.\r\n\r\nThanks!","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/911806546/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"muratmat","id":507813,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUwNzgxMw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/507813?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat","html_url":"https://github.com/muratmat","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muratmat/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/911821989","html_url":"https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6643#issuecomment-911821989","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/6643","id":911821989,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAFH-b842WUyl","user":{"login":"obigu","id":1794492,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE3OTQ0OTI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1794492?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu","html_url":"https://github.com/obigu","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/obigu/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-09-02T15:44:05Z","updated_at":"2021-09-02T15:44:25Z","body":"You don't need to worry about how the device is normally held (the \"natural or native orientation\"), the iOS API tells you how it's being currently held, that's what you want to know.\r\n\r\nIf you check `getRotation()` implementation, iOS doesn't return an angle but an orientation and on iOS \"Portrait\" always means width < height and \"Landscape\" width > height (it's also how we generally define portrait and landscape when we talk). So, following your example, if `getRotation()` has returned `90` you know for sure the device is in `Landscape` 